<paragraph blockId="24.[151,594,404,430]" box="[151,594,404,430]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,594,404,430]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,594,404,430]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">
Variation in 
<taxonomicName box="[308,594,404,430]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Pseudocalotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavigula">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[308,594,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">Pseudocalotes flavigula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,474,1039]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[151,303,474,499]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" refString="Smith, M. A. (1924) Two new lizards and a new tree frog from the Malay Peninsula. Journal of the Federated States Museum. 11, 183 - 186." type="journal article" year="1924">
Smith (
<number box="[236,295,475,499]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" value="1924.0">1924</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[431,704,474,499]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Pseudocalotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavigula">
<emphasis box="[431,704,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">Pseudocalotes flavigula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single specimen collected from the mossy forest along Brinchang Trail in Cameron Highlands (
<figureCitation box="[606,689,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1094,1948]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,1094,1948]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13. Mossy forest habitat of Pseudocalotes flavigula at Brinchang Trail, Cameron Highlands, Pahang, Peninsular Malaysia. Photograph by L. Lee Grismer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256768/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">
Fig. 
<number box="[659,689,511,535]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Smith’s (
<number box="[812,871,511,535]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" value="1924.0">1924</number>
) description was rather brief but was significantly augmented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Grismer" box="[322,498,546,571]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" refString="Grismer, L. L., Quah, E. S. H., Siler, C. D., Chan, K. O., Wood, P. L. Jr., Grismer, J. L., Anuar, S. &amp; Norhayati, A. (2011) Peninsular Malaysia's first limbless lizard: a new species of the genus Larutia (Bohme) from Pulau Pinang with a phylogeny of the genus. Zootaxa, 2799, 29 - 40." type="journal article" year="2011">
Grismer (
<number box="[432,490,547,571]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
with the examination of another specimen collected from Brinchang Trail (
<collectionCode box="[1380,1436,547,571]" country="Singapore" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/16z4-1tbx" name="Zoological Reference Collection, National University of Singapore" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">ZRC</collectionCode>
<number box="[151,230,582,607]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" value="2.5162">2.5162</number>
) reported by (
<bibRefCitation author="Leong" box="[407,550,583,607]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" refString="Leong, T. M. (2001) A first female topotype of the montane agamid Pseudocalotes flavigula (Smith, 1924) from Peninsular Malaysia, with description of coloration in life. Hamadryad, 26, 364 - 366." type="journal article" year="2001">
Leong 
<number box="[493,550,583,607]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and an additional specimen from Tanah Rata (
<collectionCode box="[1133,1216,583,607]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34795" name="Field Museum of Natural History" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">FMNH</collectionCode>
<number box="[1229,1318,583,607]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" value="143903.0">143903</number>
). Meristic variation among five of the six known specimens is presented in 
<tableCitation box="[887,974,618,643]" captionStart="TABLE 5" captionStartId="21.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1387,274,2030]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="TABLE 5. Diagnostic morphological and color pattern characters separating Psedocalotes flavigula and P. v i s e r i on sp. nov." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/73F36677FFA1FFB02DA3B8BA01BA68ED" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" tableUuid="73F36677FFA1FFB02DA3B8BA01BA68ED">
Table 
<number box="[957,974,618,643]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" value="5.0">5</number>
</tableCitation>
. The color pattern in 
<taxonomicName box="[1218,1346,618,643]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Pseudocalotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavigula">
<emphasis box="[1218,1346,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">P. flavigula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite variable (
<figureCitation box="[259,345,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1364,1386]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1342]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1343]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12. Pseudocalotes flavigula from Cameron Highlands, Pahang, Peninsular Malaysia. Upper left: Juvenile from Tanah Rata (LSUDPC 9902, photo by Zhaharil Dzulkafly). Middle left; Adult female from Brinchang Trail (LSUDPC 4350, photo by Leong Tzi Ming). Lower left and right: Adult male from Tanah Rata (LSUHC 12420, photo by L. Lee Grismer). Upper right and middle, respectively: Adult females from Tanah Rata (LSUHC 12581) and Brinchang Trail (LSUHC 12580); photos by Evan S. H. Quah." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256767/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">
Fig. 
<number box="[314,345,655,679]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). The dark, dorsal bands range from brown to black and from to distinct and diffuse to barely visible. The light-colored upper lip, lateral throat and proximal section of the brachium can range from immaculate white to lime-green and it may or may not extend onto the anterior portion of the flanks. There is considerable variation in overall ground color that ranges from dull-white to lime-green which we attribute to substrate matching (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1364,1386]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1342]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1343]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12. Pseudocalotes flavigula from Cameron Highlands, Pahang, Peninsular Malaysia. Upper left: Juvenile from Tanah Rata (LSUDPC 9902, photo by Zhaharil Dzulkafly). Middle left; Adult female from Brinchang Trail (LSUDPC 4350, photo by Leong Tzi Ming). Lower left and right: Adult male from Tanah Rata (LSUHC 12420, photo by L. Lee Grismer). Upper right and middle, respectively: Adult females from Tanah Rata (LSUHC 12581) and Brinchang Trail (LSUHC 12580); photos by Evan S. H. Quah." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256767/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,243,799,823]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,474,1039]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">
We obtained a series of close-up photographs of a juvenile male 
<taxonomicName box="[931,1093,834,859]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Pseudocalotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[931,1093,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">Pseudocalotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode box="[1107,1211,835,859]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">THNHM</collectionCode>
<number box="[1220,1292,834,859]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" value="25890.0">25890</number>
) collected at 
<quantity box="[151,238,871,895]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" unit="m" value="1400.0">1400 m</quantity>
in elevation from a montane region in the Hala-Bala Wildlife Sanctuary, Betong District, Yala Province, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,251,906,931]" name="Thailand" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">Thailand</collectingCountry>
along the Thai-Malay border. This habitat is contiguous with the Banjaran Titiwangsa and the data taken from the photographs—most notably the color pattern and the enlarged, plate-like flank scales (
<figureCitation box="[1241,1321,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1091,1113]" captionTargetBox="[157,1434,193,1053]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[157,1442,193,1053]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 14. Pseudocalotes sp. nov., from the Hala-Bala Wildlife Sanctuary, Betong District, Yala Province, Thailand. Photograph by Sunchai Makchai." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256769/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">
Fig. 
<number box="[1295,1321,942,967]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
)—clearly align this specimen with the 
<emphasis box="[476,675,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">flavigula-viserion</emphasis>
clade but until the specimen can be examined it will be recognized here as 
<taxonomicName box="[236,398,1014,1039]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Pseudocalotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[236,398,1014,1039]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">Pseudocalotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[405,494,1015,1039]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[405,494,1015,1039]" pageId="24" pageNumber="485">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
